###
# Flux Framework - Greeting Feature API Tests
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code
###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1. Public Endpoint (No Auth Required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/greeting/hello

### 2. Personalized Greeting with Name
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/greeting/greet/John
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Welcome"
}

### 3. Invalid Name (Should fail validation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/greeting/greet/A
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Hi"
}

### 4. Authenticated Endpoint (Requires JWT Token)
# Note: This will fail until you have authentication setup
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/greeting/personal
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Admin Endpoint (Requires Admin Role)
# Note: This will fail until you have authentication + admin role
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/greeting/admin
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###
# To test authenticated endpoints:
# 1. Set up JWT_SECRET in .env file
# 2. Create a user registration/login endpoint
# 3. Get JWT token from login
# 4. Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with actual token
###